<div class="reveal" id="article6">
 <div class="hobbytipsheading"><h3 class="heading"> Our own Personal Cubbies! </h3></div>
 <div class="articleintro"><div class="introwords"><p class="tipheading">By Jamie Vaughan - 19th January 2022</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;What does your workspace look like?<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In light of Lee recently starting the process of upgrading his attic space into a fully fledged model-making haven, we asked members of the Cubby's facebook group, "What does your workspace look like?" Well, a picture speaks a thousand words, so here is what the cubby replied with! Starting with my own little workspace (picture on the right). Including posable LED lamp and home made paints rack.</p></div><div class="picboxright"><span class="authorborder"><img class="cubbyimg" src="images/workspaces/Jamie's cubby.jpg" class="authorpic" title="Jamie's Cubby" alt="Jamie's Cubby"></span><div class="central"><p class="picheading">Jamie's Cubby</p></div></div></div>
 
 <div class="section1"><div class="picboxleft"><img class="cubbyimg" src="images/workspaces/Adam's mancave.jpg" title="Adam's Mancave" alt="Adam's Mancave"><div class="central"><p class="picheading">Adam's Mancave</p></div></div>
 <div class="sectionwords"><p>This is the indoor mancave of Adam Halford. As you can see he is very organised and and has nice bit of space to work with. Nice tanks on display!</p></div></div>
 <div class="section2"><div class="sectionwords"><p>Alice's "Craft Room", multi-functional, super clean and tidy, lot's of desk space to lay your work out and have a good look at what's going on. I approve Alice!</p></div>
 <div class="picboxright"><img class="cubbyimg" src="images/workspaces/Alice Mundy.jpg" title="Alice Mundy" alt="Alice Mundy"><div class="central"><p class="picheading">Alice Mundy</p></div></div></div>
 <div class="section1"><div class="picboxleft"><img class="cubbyimg" src="images/workspaces/Darren's chaos.jpg" title="Darren's Chaos" alt="Darren's Chaos"><div class="central"><p class="picheading">Darren's Chaos</p></div></div>
 <div class="sectionwords"><p>Darren Hoyle describes this as chaos, but we can all see how practical this set up is. Nice to see a spray booth for airbrushing, and PC monitor for info and entertainment. We love it!</p></div></div>
 <div class="section2"><div class="sectionwords"><p>"This is the place where Karin Schwarzenberg and I transform thoughts into objects. It's the place where people normally enjoy their dinner, but not us... It's not the place where things disappear anymore, like meals and things like that, but here in our apartment it's the place where things are born, created, built and painted. We just turned the energy of that space around.☺️".</p></div>
 <div class="picboxright"><img class="cubbyimg" src="images/workspaces/Debby Veer.jpg" title="Debby Veer" alt="Debby Veer"><div class="central"><p class="picheading">Debby Veer</p></div></div></div>
 <div class="section1"><div class="picboxleft"><img class="cubbyimg" src="images/workspaces/Nigel's cubby.jpg" title="Nigel's Cubby" alt="Nigel's Cubby"><div class="central"><p class="picheading">Nigel's Cubby</p></div></div>
 <div class="sectionwords"><p>Nigel J Goodson - a well loved but also very organised workspace</p></div></div>
 <div class="section2"><div class="sectionwords"><p>"I tidied up for the photo 😉😆"</p></div>
 <div class="picboxright"><img class="cubbyimg" src="images/workspaces/David King on a tidy day.jpg" title="David King on a tidy day" alt="David King on a tidy day"><div class="central"><p class="picheading">David King on a tidy day</p></div></div></div>
 <div class="section1"><div class="picboxleft"><img class="cubbyimg" src="images/workspaces/Samuel Patrick Matthews.jpg" title="Samuel Patrick Matthews" alt="Samuel Patrick Matthews"><div class="central"><p class="picheading">Samuel Patrick Matthews</p></div></div>
 <div class="sectionwords"><p>"This is mine; it's a bit crammped but serves a purpose. If we are able to buy this house we're in, I'll be sorting the loft into a proper man cave. It's also massively important to put your own personal touches on it."</p></div></div>
 <div class="section2"><div class="sectionwords"><p>"I'm in the basement ... got stereo ... got records ... wife throws down a Cup O' Noodles every couple of hours ... I'm a happy camper 🙂"</p></div>
 <div class="picboxright"><img class="cubbyimg" src="images/workspaces/Stuart Povick.jpg" title="Stuart Povick" alt="Stuart Povick"><div class="central"><p class="picheading">Stuart Povick</p></div></div></div>
 <div class="section1"><div class="picboxleft"><img class="cubbyimg" src="images/workspaces/Lee's cubby.jpg" title="Lee's cubby" alt="Lee's cubby"><div class="central"><p class="picheading">Lee's Cubby-to-be</p></div></div>
 <div class="sectionwords"><p>And last but not least, Lee's future Cubby Hole! <br><br>"I’m going to paint the bricks and I have a breathable fabric to staple over the joists. I’m told it’s important to retain airflow. Although I have discovered a way I can line the roof with hardboard as long as I leave an air gap at the eves." <br><br> I can see your new spray booth there Lee, very nice! And some great potential for situational shelving going on.</p></div></div>
 
</div>

